2
00:00:17.880 --> 00:00:22.010
Setting out before the day breaks

3
00:00:18.390 --> 00:00:22.120
Yoru ga akeru mae ni tabidatou

4
00:00:21.720 --> 00:00:26.520
To greet an unknown tomorrow

5
00:00:22.240 --> 00:00:26.490
Mada minu ashita wo mukae ni ikou

6
00:00:26.270 --> 00:00:30.100
We have no regrets in our resolve

7
00:00:26.790 --> 00:00:30.290
Sou kimeta koto kui wa nai

8
00:00:29.900 --> 00:00:33.190
(Oh, I know what I’m supposed to do)

9
00:00:32.860 --> 00:00:36.860
No matter what kind of trials lie ahead,

10
00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:36.980
Donna shiren ga machiukete iyouto

11
00:00:36.530 --> 00:00:41.460
Nothing can stop my throbbing heart

12
00:00:37.030 --> 00:00:41.490
Takanaru kodou tomerare wa shinai

13
00:00:41.070 --> 00:00:46.160
There is only one place to go

14
00:00:41.590 --> 00:00:46.130
Mezasu basho wa tada hitotsu

15
00:00:45.870 --> 00:00:48.070
(Fly to the light)

16
00:00:47.620 --> 00:00:51.790
Bonds forged through battle

17
00:00:48.140 --> 00:00:51.770
Tatakai no hate ni eta kizuna

18
00:00:51.420 --> 00:00:55.500
I won’t let anyone get hurt

19
00:00:51.940 --> 00:00:55.540
Dare nimo kizutsukesase wa shinai

20
00:00:55.090 --> 00:00:58.300
When I open my clenched fist,

21
00:00:55.600 --> 00:00:58.370
Nigiri shimeta te hirakeba

22
00:00:57.880 --> 00:01:01.550
I will find power there

23
00:00:58.400 --> 00:01:01.610
Soko ni chikara ga yadoru

24
00:01:01.220 --> 00:01:03.930
So let’s start

25
00:01:01.710 --> 00:01:03.980
Saa hajimeyou

26
00:01:03.600 --> 00:01:09.100
The new world is calling

27
00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:09.110
Atarashii sekai ga yondeiru

28
00:01:08.680 --> 00:01:11.480
See now look

29
00:01:09.180 --> 00:01:11.580
Hora mite goran

30
00:01:11.060 --> 00:01:17.860
No matter how many seas separate us

31
00:01:11.580 --> 00:01:17.950
Ikutsu no umi hedatete itato shitemo

32
00:01:17.530 --> 00:01:21.610
I’ve always got your back

33
00:01:18.020 --> 00:01:21.590
Itsudatte sasaeteiru

34
00:01:21.110 --> 00:01:25.280
Don’t be afraid to advance

35
00:01:21.610 --> 00:01:25.580
Osorezu ni mae e

36
00:01:25.280 --> 00:01:27.650
Don’t forget

37
00:01:25.790 --> 00:01:27.650
Wasurenaide

38
00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:29.040
We fight together

39
00:01:29.160 --> 00:01:36.960
I’ve never spoiled the memory

40
00:01:29.650 --> 00:01:37.060
Kegashita koto wa nai

41
00:01:36.840 --> 00:01:39.670
Of the vast infinite sky,

42
00:01:37.360 --> 00:01:39.800
Ano hi miageta

43
00:01:39.300 --> 00:01:44.800
That I gazed upon that day

44
00:01:39.800 --> 00:01:44.800
Dokomademo takaku hiroi sora

45
00:01:44.340 --> 00:01:48.270
We’ve come a long way

46
00:01:44.830 --> 00:01:48.370
Zuibun to tooku made kita

47
00:01:47.970 --> 00:01:52.170
Each with our own pledges in our hearts

48
00:01:48.470 --> 00:01:52.170
Sorezore no chikai wo mune ni

49
00:01:51.730 --> 00:01:54.770
There is no doubt

50
00:01:52.240 --> 00:01:54.770
Mayoi nado nai

51
00:01:54.350 --> 00:01:59.230
There are burdens we must bear

52
00:01:54.840 --> 00:01:59.200
Seou mono ga aru

53
00:01:58.860 --> 00:02:01.740
The sun will rise

54
00:01:59.370 --> 00:02:01.710
Hi ga nobori

55
00:02:01.360 --> 00:02:06.660
And even illuminate our sorrows

56
00:02:01.860 --> 00:02:06.780
Kanashimi sae hitoshiku terasu

57
00:02:06.330 --> 00:02:09.080
Yes, I believe it!

58
00:02:06.810 --> 00:02:09.210
Shinjiterunda

59
00:02:08.790 --> 00:02:15.500
One Piece will someday bind us together

60
00:02:09.280 --> 00:02:15.640
Itsuka hitotsu ni tsunagaru mirai wo

61
00:02:15.130 --> 00:02:19.090
Let’s go and find it!

62
00:02:15.640 --> 00:02:19.320
Issho ni mitsuke ni ikou

63
00:02:18.840 --> 00:02:22.880
You’re irreplaceable

64
00:02:19.340 --> 00:02:23.510
Kimi no kawari wa inai

65
00:02:23.180 --> 00:02:25.050
Don’t forget

66
00:02:23.690 --> 00:02:25.350
Wasurenaide

67
00:02:24.930 --> 00:02:27.430
We fight together

68
00:02:36.450 --> 00:02:37.710
Run, Luffy!

69
00:02:44.900 --> 00:02:46.930
No... No way!

70
00:02:47.530 --> 00:02:49.600
I can't believe it!

71
00:02:49.920 --> 00:02:51.560
Captain, we're screwed!

72
00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:55.200
Sabo's Sea

73
00:02:51.560 --> 00:02:53.540
There's no way to put out the fire!

74
00:02:53.540 --> 00:02:57.120
We gotta give up the ship!
We can't flee to the sea!

75
00:02:57.120 --> 00:03:00.930
Damn that king! How could he do this to us?!

76
00:03:00.930 --> 00:03:03.160
I'll show that bastard!

77
00:03:06.400 --> 00:03:07.910
Honestly!

78
00:03:07.910 --> 00:03:13.640
It's so annoying that the sky
in the south is bright even during the night.

79
00:03:13.640 --> 00:03:17.380
Apologies, Your Majesty.
Allow us to close the curtains.

80
00:03:22.530 --> 00:03:27.620
Father, is there a reason the people
in Gray Terminal aren't humans?

81
00:03:27.620 --> 00:03:29.790
Why do they have to get burned?

82
00:03:29.790 --> 00:03:34.420
It is said, "As a man sows, so shall he reap."

83
00:03:34.420 --> 00:03:35.660
Think about it.

84
00:03:35.660 --> 00:03:40.970
They could have avoided their fate
if only they were born nobles.

85
00:03:41.400 --> 00:03:43.180
Born nobles?

86
00:03:44.050 --> 00:03:48.480
You're right! They should have
chosen to be born nobles!

87
00:03:49.170 --> 00:03:50.440
How dumb of them!

88
00:03:50.440 --> 00:03:55.020
Now, enough about those people.
You have to study tomorrow, don't you?

89
00:03:55.020 --> 00:03:56.550
You'd better get to bed.

90
00:03:56.550 --> 00:03:58.150
Okay!

91
00:03:58.150 --> 00:03:59.990
Goodnight.

92
00:04:17.080 --> 00:04:18.640
This side's blocked, too!

93
00:04:18.640 --> 00:04:21.050
We're losing ground to stand on!

94
00:04:21.050 --> 00:04:22.840
I don't wanna die here!

95
00:04:25.310 --> 00:04:27.910
Think those old guys got out okay?

96
00:04:27.910 --> 00:04:30.480
We can't worry about anyone else right now!

97
00:04:31.440 --> 00:04:34.190
Crap! I don't even know where we are!

98
00:04:34.190 --> 00:04:37.120
Who said you brats could escape?!

99
00:04:39.270 --> 00:04:40.490
Bluejam!

100
00:04:42.950 --> 00:04:46.070
Why are you still here after setting the fire?!

101
00:04:46.070 --> 00:04:48.170
You should be long gone by now!

102
00:04:48.670 --> 00:04:50.560
Shut up, you little shit!

103
00:04:51.370 --> 00:04:54.110
We're at our wits' end, you see.

104
00:04:55.170 --> 00:04:57.580
We're in a bit of a pickle.

105
00:04:58.520 --> 00:05:01.750
Humans are strange creatures, aren't they?

106
00:05:03.140 --> 00:05:06.820
When you hit rock bottom,
you can't stop laughing.

107
00:05:14.310 --> 00:05:16.760
They're being weird.

108
00:05:17.650 --> 00:05:18.660
Luffy! We gotta run!

109
00:05:18.660 --> 00:05:20.230
Stop them!

110
00:05:28.540 --> 00:05:32.350
We worked together as crewmates, after all!

111
00:05:32.350 --> 00:05:34.540
Now, we need to die together!

112
00:05:34.540 --> 00:05:38.490
We're not gonna die with you!
Never in a million years!

113
00:05:38.490 --> 00:05:40.150
Cold shoulder, huh?

114
00:05:40.150 --> 00:05:45.690
Come to think of it, you still haven't
told me where you stash your treasure.

115
00:05:46.370 --> 00:05:51.530
I'll rescue it from the fire for you.
So, tell me where it is!

116
00:05:51.530 --> 00:05:54.730
You're about to die and all you
care about is treasure?!

117
00:05:54.730 --> 00:05:58.180
Well, if you don't care, then tell me.

118
00:06:00.660 --> 00:06:02.840
You've really lost it.

119
00:06:03.070 --> 00:06:06.880
Not salvaging it would be such a waste!

120
00:06:06.880 --> 00:06:12.050
If we just stand here, it'll get
reduced to charcoal like my ship!

121
00:06:12.050 --> 00:06:14.220
What a waste.

122
00:06:14.710 --> 00:06:17.250
Don't be dumb! That treasure is–

123
00:06:17.250 --> 00:06:19.380
Fine! I'll tell you.

124
00:06:19.890 --> 00:06:24.140
Ace! You and Sabo worked so long to–

125
00:06:24.140 --> 00:06:26.340
Sabo would understand!

126
00:06:27.370 --> 00:06:29.090
Right now your life...

127
00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:33.040
Right now our lives are more important!

128
00:06:39.700 --> 00:06:41.530
Ace...

129
00:06:49.490 --> 00:06:53.830
We have six-years-worth
of treasure in this tree.

130
00:06:53.830 --> 00:06:55.370
I see.

131
00:06:56.780 --> 00:06:58.290
Don't cry!

132
00:06:58.290 --> 00:07:01.710
It's all right. This isn't where it ends.

133
00:07:07.350 --> 00:07:10.180
What're you doing?! I told you where it is!

134
00:07:10.180 --> 00:07:13.030
You're right. "This isn't where it ends."

135
00:07:13.890 --> 00:07:17.880
There's a chance you lied,
so you're coming with us!

136
00:07:17.880 --> 00:07:22.500
No way! We'll lose our
chance to get out of here!

137
00:07:22.500 --> 00:07:23.890
Just go on your own!

138
00:07:27.750 --> 00:07:31.860
You don't wanna mess with me right now.

139
00:07:31.860 --> 00:07:35.070
Even if it means robbing a few kids,

140
00:07:35.070 --> 00:07:40.880
I swore I'd make a comeback
and get my revenge on the nobles.

141
00:07:40.880 --> 00:07:43.740
And your brother is one of them.

142
00:07:43.740 --> 00:07:47.580
They think they're so special,

143
00:07:48.050 --> 00:07:51.850
looking down on us like
we're nothing but trash!

144
00:07:51.850 --> 00:07:54.520
Sabo doesn't think like that!

145
00:07:54.520 --> 00:07:57.160
He's no different, you idiot kid!

146
00:07:57.830 --> 00:08:02.090
He spent time with you
because it made him feel superior!

147
00:08:02.090 --> 00:08:03.760
That's not true!

148
00:08:04.410 --> 00:08:06.740
His parents are loaded.

149
00:08:06.740 --> 00:08:09.200
He wants for nothing!

150
00:08:09.520 --> 00:08:12.470
This was all a cheap thrill for him.

151
00:08:12.470 --> 00:08:17.280
He was looking down at you,
holding his nose while laughing to himself!

152
00:08:17.280 --> 00:08:19.910
Stop badmouthing Sabo!

153
00:08:19.910 --> 00:08:22.920
Yeah, Sabo just wants to be free!

154
00:08:24.220 --> 00:08:26.020
You little shit!

155
00:08:26.020 --> 00:08:26.890
Luffy!

156
00:08:31.220 --> 00:08:32.660
I'm gonna kill you!

157
00:08:36.880 --> 00:08:38.090
Let go of me!

158
00:08:41.900 --> 00:08:44.500
Don't you touch Luffy!

159
00:09:14.470 --> 00:09:15.900
Luffy! You okay?!

160
00:09:18.030 --> 00:09:19.700
What did you do?!

161
00:09:22.240 --> 00:09:24.140
Dammit...

162
00:09:24.140 --> 00:09:26.470
Sneaky runt!

163
00:09:26.950 --> 00:09:30.010
You looking to make a fool outta me too?!

164
00:09:30.010 --> 00:09:32.310
Shut up, scumbag!

165
00:09:33.220 --> 00:09:35.390
You bastard!

166
00:09:36.270 --> 00:09:38.400
Ace!

167
00:09:38.400 --> 00:09:40.660
Don't do it!

168
00:09:52.500 --> 00:09:53.340
Dadan!

169
00:09:55.310 --> 00:09:58.310
Stop it, you sea monster!

170
00:10:00.810 --> 00:10:03.710
Let go of Ace!

171
00:10:14.940 --> 00:10:16.460
Why are you guys here?!

172
00:10:17.120 --> 00:10:18.500
We finally found you!

173
00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:22.870
These are pretty serious wounds,
Luffy! Are you okay?

174
00:10:23.560 --> 00:10:25.390
Dogra...

175
00:10:26.710 --> 00:10:29.610
I don't see Sabo anywhere!

176
00:10:29.610 --> 00:10:33.210
Sabo went home. He's not here.

177
00:10:37.940 --> 00:10:39.430
Ace!

178
00:10:39.430 --> 00:10:42.970
You must be that
boss monkey from Mt. Colubo!

179
00:10:42.970 --> 00:10:45.100
I'm the mountain bandit, Dadan!

180
00:10:45.100 --> 00:10:49.930
I'm not sure why, but for better
or worse, I foster these brats!

181
00:10:55.300 --> 00:10:56.840
Alright, fellas...

182
00:11:01.960 --> 00:11:03.480
Make a run for it!

183
00:11:03.480 --> 00:11:05.410
– You got it, boss!
– You got it, boss!

184
00:11:06.860 --> 00:11:08.910
Hey, what're you doing?!

185
00:11:08.910 --> 00:11:11.080
Ace, hurry up!

186
00:11:11.530 --> 00:11:12.680
Ace!

187
00:11:13.290 --> 00:11:14.320
I...

188
00:11:16.940 --> 00:11:18.560
won't run!

189
00:11:20.190 --> 00:11:24.430
What're you saying, Ace?!
Don't try to fight him!

190
00:11:24.630 --> 00:11:27.570
Bluejam's a real villain!

191
00:11:27.570 --> 00:11:31.240
Kids like you couldn't possibly
beat a guy like him!

192
00:11:31.240 --> 00:11:32.940
M-Me too!

193
00:11:32.940 --> 00:11:34.820
No, Luffy!

194
00:11:38.040 --> 00:11:41.980
You guys... Take Luffy and go on ahead!

195
00:11:41.980 --> 00:11:43.320
B-Boss!

196
00:11:43.720 --> 00:11:47.840
As for me, I'm bringing Ace back home!

197
00:11:49.190 --> 00:11:50.960
– Boss!
– Boss!

198
00:11:52.360 --> 00:11:53.730
Get going!

199
00:11:53.730 --> 00:11:54.860
– Y-Yes, ma'am!
– Y-Yes, ma'am!

200
00:11:54.860 --> 00:11:56.480
Ace!

201
00:11:56.480 --> 00:12:00.070
Boss! You'd better make it back!

202
00:12:04.120 --> 00:12:06.570
A woman and a child.

203
00:12:07.830 --> 00:12:13.140
If you overestimate your abilities,
you'll pay in blood!

204
00:12:13.820 --> 00:12:18.020
Only the strong and the cowardly
survive in battle!

205
00:12:18.660 --> 00:12:22.210
The brave always die.

206
00:12:22.890 --> 00:12:24.900
Is that so?

207
00:12:25.580 --> 00:12:26.660
Fools!

208
00:12:36.740 --> 00:12:40.240
Damn!

209
00:12:40.240 --> 00:12:44.400
We're goners! The flames are all around us!

210
00:12:44.400 --> 00:12:46.950
How could this happen to us?!

211
00:12:46.950 --> 00:12:49.320
It's hot! It's hot!

212
00:12:49.320 --> 00:12:51.280
There's no way out!

213
00:12:53.520 --> 00:12:54.910
Dammit!

214
00:12:55.650 --> 00:12:57.720
There's nothing we can do!

215
00:13:22.640 --> 00:13:24.620
What just happened?

216
00:13:25.510 --> 00:13:27.190
There's a path!

217
00:13:27.370 --> 00:13:29.850
That explosion made a path!

218
00:13:29.850 --> 00:13:31.990
Whatever the reason, we're in luck!

219
00:13:31.990 --> 00:13:36.100
Hey! Look! It's a ship!

220
00:13:36.100 --> 00:13:37.860
I see a ship!

221
00:13:37.860 --> 00:13:40.430
This path leads up to the shore!

222
00:13:40.430 --> 00:13:42.990
We can follow it out of here!

223
00:13:43.390 --> 00:13:47.040
Run before the fire returns!

224
00:13:49.940 --> 00:13:55.210
Vhaat an awful country,
burning the land and its residents!

225
00:13:55.450 --> 00:13:57.490
By the vayy,

226
00:13:57.490 --> 00:14:02.260
vhyy did you know the goings on of
such a remote kingdom in the East Blue?

227
00:14:02.740 --> 00:14:06.320
Vhaat is so special about this place, hm?

228
00:14:06.320 --> 00:14:10.330
This country is a microcosm
of our world's future.

229
00:14:10.570 --> 00:14:16.630
Happiness is but a pipe dream in a world
that eliminates those deemed unnecessary.

230
00:14:16.630 --> 00:14:21.670
I swear to you all,
I will change this world someday!

231
00:14:21.780 --> 00:14:27.820
If I stay here... I'll never be free!

232
00:14:28.470 --> 00:14:33.050
Even in a country like this,
children will be born.

233
00:14:44.660 --> 00:14:51.600
Those of you who are willing to fight by my
side for freedom, come aboard my ship!

234
00:14:54.170 --> 00:14:57.080
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

235
00:14:57.110 --> 00:14:59.860
Royal Palace
Goa Kingdom

236
00:15:04.860 --> 00:15:10.220
Is the town really safe? The flames look like
they could consume us at any moment!

237
00:15:12.960 --> 00:15:17.300
Is there any chance they'd
let us up into High Town?

238
00:15:17.300 --> 00:15:18.650
Zero.

239
00:15:19.230 --> 00:15:22.900
Not even a bug could enter—nobles only!

240
00:15:22.900 --> 00:15:27.610
– Boss!
– Boss!

241
00:15:28.080 --> 00:15:29.810
Ace!

242
00:15:29.810 --> 00:15:31.900
Boss!

243
00:15:31.900 --> 00:15:34.200
– Ace!
– Ace!

244
00:15:34.200 --> 00:15:36.970
Boss!

245
00:15:38.220 --> 00:15:40.720
Ace and Dadan...

246
00:15:40.720 --> 00:15:47.460
did not return from
the flames of Gray Terminal.

247
00:15:51.360 --> 00:15:53.420
Take it easy and wait, Luffy.

248
00:15:53.420 --> 00:15:55.670
Where are you going in that condition?

249
00:15:55.670 --> 00:15:58.690
I'm gonna go look for Ace and Dadan!

250
00:15:58.690 --> 00:16:00.220
Don't be so reckless!

251
00:16:01.940 --> 00:16:06.680
Your wounds are really deep. Just take it easy and relax.

252
00:16:06.680 --> 00:16:13.480
Right now, Gray Terminal is crawling
with soldiers cleaning up after the fire.

253
00:16:13.480 --> 00:16:18.160
And they're not just
"cleaning up" the burned trash...

254
00:16:18.160 --> 00:16:21.230
they're "cleaning up" any survivors
they find as well.

255
00:16:21.230 --> 00:16:23.990
If you go there now, you'll get killed.

256
00:16:23.990 --> 00:16:25.530
But...!

257
00:16:35.840 --> 00:16:38.540
I wanna see Ace!

258
00:16:38.540 --> 00:16:42.640
I'm sure Sabo's worried about us too!

259
00:16:45.480 --> 00:16:47.650
The Remains of Gray Terminal

260
00:16:51.360 --> 00:16:54.930
Our orders are to shoot any survivors on sight.

261
00:16:54.930 --> 00:16:56.690
As if anyone survived this!

262
00:16:57.030 --> 00:17:00.050
Still, I expected a lot more corpses than this...

263
00:17:00.050 --> 00:17:03.400
It was one hell of a fire!
It must've torched them, bones and all.

264
00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:11.640
I was really worried that the fire would
jump the wall and reach the city yesterday.

265
00:17:11.640 --> 00:17:14.380
I heard even Bluejam's ship caught fire.

266
00:17:14.380 --> 00:17:18.820
I'm glad those no-good thugs
didn't escape the blaze.

267
00:17:24.320 --> 00:17:27.390
Run all you want, you can't get away, Sabo!

268
00:17:27.970 --> 00:17:33.030
The entire military and every single
police officer have your picture now!

269
00:17:33.030 --> 00:17:36.460
You will never get out of High Town...

270
00:17:36.460 --> 00:17:38.070
much less this house!

271
00:17:39.500 --> 00:17:44.900
Discard those uniforms. From here on,
you two work for me as his bodyguards.

272
00:17:44.900 --> 00:17:46.980
But sir, our duties...

273
00:17:46.980 --> 00:17:50.770
Nothing is beyond a nobleman's power.

274
00:17:50.770 --> 00:17:53.340
I'll get the approval of your superiors.

275
00:17:57.020 --> 00:18:03.730
You will hole up in your room and fully
educate yourself in your role as a noble.

276
00:18:03.730 --> 00:18:04.560
No!

277
00:18:04.560 --> 00:18:10.540
As I've told you, all it takes is
a single word to get what I want.

278
00:18:10.540 --> 00:18:14.730
Imagine what I could do to you...
or to your two friends.

279
00:18:15.390 --> 00:18:17.110
Understood?

280
00:18:18.270 --> 00:18:19.770
Dad...

281
00:18:22.160 --> 00:18:25.780
Ace... Luffy...

282
00:18:30.050 --> 00:18:36.330
If you understand, then commit to
a change of heart and study hard like Sterry.

283
00:18:36.330 --> 00:18:43.870
And now, go forth and study; bring happiness
to the mother and father who gave you life.

284
00:18:44.650 --> 00:18:48.070
This, in turn, is your happiness.

285
00:18:48.070 --> 00:18:50.070
Do you not agree?

286
00:18:52.340 --> 00:18:54.370
Father!

287
00:18:55.920 --> 00:18:58.180
Don't worry! I'm here for you!

288
00:19:00.330 --> 00:19:02.740
You're so dependable, Sterry!

289
00:19:02.740 --> 00:19:05.620
Alright! I'll buy you a marvelous new outfit!

290
00:19:05.620 --> 00:19:07.950
The ceremony is in two days, after all.

291
00:19:07.950 --> 00:19:10.840
There, we will see the
Celestial Dragon in person!

292
00:19:19.720 --> 00:19:22.970
Make sure you have your
homework finished by tomorrow.

293
00:19:23.340 --> 00:19:25.600
Well then, have a wonderful day.

294
00:19:34.660 --> 00:19:37.590
Ace... Luffy...

295
00:19:38.090 --> 00:19:42.060
There's no way you'd
die in a fire like that, right?

296
00:19:42.750 --> 00:19:45.960
You guys are safe, right?

297
00:19:56.080 --> 00:19:59.880
I really want to see you.

298
00:20:02.010 --> 00:20:07.790
But if I do, I'd only put you in danger again.

299
00:20:08.490 --> 00:20:10.490
This place is like a birdcage.

300
00:20:11.040 --> 00:20:16.750
I don't think I can even bear
to breathe its stale air any longer.

301
00:20:23.210 --> 00:20:25.950
What is freedom?

302
00:20:26.860 --> 00:20:29.650
Where can I find it?

303
00:20:32.040 --> 00:20:34.280
Well then, we're off!

304
00:20:34.700 --> 00:20:37.640
I leave Sabo in your care.

305
00:20:37.640 --> 00:20:39.650
Very well, Master.

306
00:20:59.140 --> 00:21:06.280
On this day, one of the Grand Line's very own
world nobles visits the Kingdom of Goa.

307
00:21:06.560 --> 00:21:12.110
A grand ceremony has been
prepared to welcome the ship.

308
00:21:17.340 --> 00:21:20.970
Hey, wait! Someone's boat is sailing out!

309
00:21:21.730 --> 00:21:22.470
What?

310
00:21:22.470 --> 00:21:23.330
A fishing boat?!

311
00:21:25.550 --> 00:21:30.620
Hey! Turn back! You'll disrupt the ceremony!

312
00:21:31.510 --> 00:21:33.340
It's a child!

313
00:21:33.340 --> 00:21:35.810
There's a child on the ship!

314
00:21:35.810 --> 00:21:36.980
A child?

315
00:21:36.980 --> 00:21:39.880
I wonder which family he's from.

316
00:21:39.880 --> 00:21:41.250
A child...?

317
00:21:43.040 --> 00:21:45.140
The weather's great!

318
00:21:45.140 --> 00:21:46.950
The perfect day for a voyage!

319
00:21:52.450 --> 00:21:55.720
Hey, hey! That's my ship!

320
00:21:55.720 --> 00:21:58.370
He stole my fishing boat!

321
00:21:58.370 --> 00:22:01.180
Look! He's flying a black flag!

322
00:22:01.180 --> 00:22:03.770
What, does he think he's a pirate?!

323
00:22:03.770 --> 00:22:06.470
No way! A kid by himself, a pirate?!

324
00:22:06.850 --> 00:22:09.040
Where's he heading?

325
00:22:09.040 --> 00:22:11.180
He'll get in the way of ceremony.

326
00:22:11.180 --> 00:22:14.380
The World Government ship is almost here!

327
00:22:14.380 --> 00:22:16.000
Hurry up and do something!

328
00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:17.550
Y-Yes, sir!

329
00:22:17.550 --> 00:22:19.220
Hey!

330
00:22:19.460 --> 00:22:23.190
Hey, you! Get back here this instant!

331
00:22:25.140 --> 00:22:29.990
The thing I'm most afraid of
is being consumed by this country...

332
00:22:30.600 --> 00:22:33.260
and becoming someone else!

333
00:22:36.750 --> 00:22:38.980
I'm never going back!

334
00:22:42.020 --> 00:22:45.380
That's not Sabo, is it?!

335
00:22:47.420 --> 00:22:51.340
The government ship is here!

336
00:23:09.300 --> 00:23:12.240
What a huge ship!

337
00:23:12.240 --> 00:23:14.780
Crashing into that would end things real quick.

338
00:23:15.450 --> 00:23:16.930
Let's avoid that.

339
00:23:21.820 --> 00:23:26.330
To think we get this rare chance
to lay eyes on someone so blessed!

340
00:23:26.330 --> 00:23:30.380
I can't believe an honest-to-goodness
Celestial Dragon is on that ship!

341
00:23:31.520 --> 00:23:34.130
What is that?

342
00:23:34.860 --> 00:23:37.660
It appears to be a simple fishing boat, sir.

343
00:23:41.580 --> 00:23:45.430
I can't wait to be the captain
of a ship like that someday!

344
00:24:02.060 --> 00:24:04.160
Ace isn't dead!

345
00:24:04.160 --> 00:24:08.210
I know, take it easy. I know how you feel.

346
00:24:08.210 --> 00:24:13.130
But you're in no state to go to Gray Terminal,
especially with all the troops there.

347
00:24:13.130 --> 00:24:13.900
But...!

348
00:24:13.900 --> 00:24:16.370
No buts! That fire was massive!

349
00:24:16.370 --> 00:24:23.940
And chances are slim... but we all want
to believe that the boss and Ace are alive.

350
00:24:23.940 --> 00:24:27.350
Dogra is already there searching
for them, so trust him and wait!

351
00:24:28.140 --> 00:24:32.080
We're all have a hard time, not just you, Luffy.

352
00:24:35.910 --> 00:24:37.930
The fishing boat's been hit!

353
00:24:37.930 --> 00:24:39.260
What about the kid?!

354
00:24:39.260 --> 00:24:41.890
He must've angered the Celestial Dragon!

355
00:24:42.240 --> 00:24:43.460
Sabo!

356
00:24:44.270 --> 00:24:47.500
Crap! The ship caught fire!

357
00:24:47.500 --> 00:24:48.970
Why'd they shoot me like that?!

358
00:24:49.730 --> 00:24:52.740
Saint Jalmack! There's a child on that boat!

359
00:24:52.740 --> 00:24:57.240
No matter who he is,
flying a black flag makes him a pirate.

360
00:24:57.420 --> 00:24:59.810
But most importantly...

361
00:25:04.170 --> 00:25:05.250
Dammit!

362
00:25:05.250 --> 00:25:09.750
How dare that lowly commoner
enter the path of my ship?!

363
00:25:23.370 --> 00:25:26.230
Hey! What was that ship doing?

364
00:25:26.230 --> 00:25:28.170
This is an important ceremony!

365
00:25:28.170 --> 00:25:31.680
We don't wanna put
the Celestial Dragon in a bad mood!

366
00:25:31.680 --> 00:25:34.370
Clean up that flotsam already!

367
00:25:56.780 --> 00:25:58.070
Hey!

368
00:25:58.070 --> 00:26:00.570
Hey, everyone, they're...!

369
00:26:00.570 --> 00:26:01.740
What is it?

370
00:26:02.900 --> 00:26:05.110
They're back!

371
00:26:26.000 --> 00:26:27.970
– Thank goodness!
– Thank goodness!

372
00:26:28.450 --> 00:26:31.270
Ace... Boss...

373
00:26:31.270 --> 00:26:35.240
She's severely wounded!
Hurry up and treat her!

374
00:26:35.630 --> 00:26:37.370
Are you okay?

375
00:26:39.180 --> 00:26:41.050
Ace!

376
00:26:41.580 --> 00:26:42.680
Luffy!

377
00:26:45.080 --> 00:26:48.150
Did you think I was dead?

378
00:26:48.150 --> 00:26:49.290
But...!

379
00:26:49.290 --> 00:26:50.360
Why are you crying?!

380
00:26:51.900 --> 00:26:53.900
You're acting like I died, you idiot!

381
00:26:54.440 --> 00:26:57.330
Well, now, take it easy. That's enough.

382
00:26:57.820 --> 00:26:59.960
Luffy is just happy.

383
00:27:05.780 --> 00:27:08.180
Ace, can we ask about the night of the fire?

384
00:27:08.180 --> 00:27:10.540
After we left with Luffy,

385
00:27:10.540 --> 00:27:13.660
what happened to you and the boss?

386
00:27:15.300 --> 00:27:17.950
We fought with Bluejam...

387
00:27:20.230 --> 00:27:22.160
Somehow, we managed to defeat him...

388
00:27:25.710 --> 00:27:28.920
and we hurried and tried
to catch up with you guys...

389
00:27:29.720 --> 00:27:32.080
but by then, the path was blocked.

390
00:27:32.700 --> 00:27:35.020
Dadan was badly burned.

391
00:27:35.350 --> 00:27:39.470
We hid by the river in the midway
forest, safe from the fire.

392
00:27:45.220 --> 00:27:49.400
I stole some medicine from town
and also found some food.

393
00:27:50.170 --> 00:27:53.300
It was all I could do to keep Dadan alive.

394
00:28:00.060 --> 00:28:01.910
Take it easy. I see now.

395
00:28:01.910 --> 00:28:05.290
Well, I'm glad you both made it out alive.

396
00:28:05.290 --> 00:28:07.060
Sorry to make you worry.

397
00:28:07.960 --> 00:28:11.860
It's crazy what happened to Gray Terminal...

398
00:28:11.860 --> 00:28:13.810
I'm sure Sabo is worried.

399
00:28:17.380 --> 00:28:21.480
More insolent commoners might show up.

400
00:28:21.480 --> 00:28:23.890
Remain vigilant.

401
00:28:23.890 --> 00:28:24.690
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

402
00:28:29.950 --> 00:28:32.670
I wonder what Sabo's up to.

403
00:28:32.670 --> 00:28:37.510
Still, I'm glad Ace came back,
and Dadan is getting better.

404
00:28:38.600 --> 00:28:40.970
Ace, back then...

405
00:28:42.040 --> 00:28:43.140
I...

406
00:28:43.140 --> 00:28:44.970
won't run!

407
00:28:46.090 --> 00:28:47.640
...why didn't you run?

408
00:28:48.080 --> 00:28:51.520
Sometimes, my blood just begins to boil.

409
00:28:51.520 --> 00:28:56.220
I'm afraid that if I run,
I'll lose something important.

410
00:28:56.220 --> 00:28:57.140
At that moment...

411
00:28:59.600 --> 00:29:02.940
Luffy was right behind me.

412
00:29:03.710 --> 00:29:05.970
I don't know, but I think that's why.

413
00:29:09.790 --> 00:29:13.690
Even when facing an army
with no chance at winning...

414
00:29:14.400 --> 00:29:16.910
Roger would never flee from the battle.

415
00:29:16.910 --> 00:29:19.970
Did he have death wish?
Running is a viable strategy, too.

416
00:29:19.970 --> 00:29:22.880
Regardless, he would never run away...

417
00:29:22.880 --> 00:29:25.810
because his loved ones were behind him.

418
00:29:25.810 --> 00:29:29.690
Running away with his crew meant
putting all their lives in danger.

419
00:29:29.690 --> 00:29:33.460
More accurately, it's not that he never ran...

420
00:29:33.460 --> 00:29:38.160
he just didn't want to give his enemies
a chance to go after his crew.

421
00:29:38.160 --> 00:29:41.690
When he got like that,
Roger became quite the demon.

422
00:29:41.690 --> 00:29:46.170
He was known to crush entire armies
just because they badmouthed a friend.

423
00:29:46.800 --> 00:29:51.020
Indeed, he was violent when angry.
His temper was short and he was selfish.

424
00:29:51.020 --> 00:29:56.670
However, his actions were always
motivated by a pure, childlike intention.

425
00:29:56.670 --> 00:29:59.780
I bet he had a similar upbringing to Ace.

426
00:29:59.780 --> 00:30:04.130
He truly hated the thought
of losing his loved ones.

427
00:30:07.410 --> 00:30:13.260
Despite living so recklessly, his luck kept him alive
long enough to become King of the Pirates.

428
00:30:14.260 --> 00:30:19.710
While the world saw him as the worst
of the worst, his crew trusted him implicitly.

429
00:30:19.710 --> 00:30:24.530
Even this old Marine couldn't
bring himself to hate Roger.

430
00:30:25.330 --> 00:30:28.310
That's why I decided to raise Ace.

431
00:30:28.310 --> 00:30:30.360
We're the ones raising him!

432
00:30:30.360 --> 00:30:33.150
Huh?! Got something you wanna say?!

433
00:30:33.150 --> 00:30:34.620
No. No problem.

434
00:30:35.960 --> 00:30:39.750
The people of the world still hate Roger.

435
00:30:39.750 --> 00:30:45.000
Even if Ace hates his father,
the apple still didn't fall far from the tree.

436
00:30:45.000 --> 00:30:48.800
Alright... Who's gonna win?

437
00:30:48.800 --> 00:30:50.030
Dogra!

438
00:30:51.700 --> 00:30:54.500
You went looking for Ace and Dadan, right?

439
00:30:54.500 --> 00:30:56.210
They both came home!

440
00:30:57.240 --> 00:31:01.040
They did? That's really great to hear...

441
00:31:01.630 --> 00:31:03.210
Wh-What?!

442
00:31:03.610 --> 00:31:04.650
Sabo is...

443
00:31:06.010 --> 00:31:07.380
You liar!

444
00:31:07.780 --> 00:31:09.690
Don't even joke about that!

445
00:31:09.690 --> 00:31:10.890
That's enough, Ace!

446
00:31:10.890 --> 00:31:13.730
I'm not lying or joking about it!

447
00:31:13.730 --> 00:31:17.660
It was so sudden that I doubted my own eyes!

448
00:31:17.660 --> 00:31:20.800
I kept thinking it was
some kind of bad dream!

449
00:31:20.800 --> 00:31:24.270
Cut the crap! Sabo went back
to his noble family.

450
00:31:24.270 --> 00:31:26.790
How could he be at sea?!

451
00:31:26.790 --> 00:31:28.740
That's right! Sabo went back ho–

452
00:31:28.740 --> 00:31:32.070
As an outlaw, I understand
how he must have felt!

453
00:31:32.070 --> 00:31:34.570
We all have places we really
don't want to go back to!

454
00:31:35.710 --> 00:31:41.120
Do you think he would've
set sail if he was truly happy?

455
00:31:41.120 --> 00:31:45.890
Do you really think he'd fly
a pirate flag and set out on his own?!

456
00:31:56.410 --> 00:31:57.660
Sabo...

457
00:31:58.530 --> 00:32:01.280
He really wasn't happy!

458
00:32:03.100 --> 00:32:06.490
Even with parents, I was all by myself.

459
00:32:06.680 --> 00:32:11.170
Why... Why didn't we try
to break him out of there?!

460
00:32:12.020 --> 00:32:16.600
Where's the guy who did this
to Sabo?! I'm gonna murder him!

461
00:32:16.600 --> 00:32:19.350
Th-The Celestial Dragon?!
There's no way you can do th–

462
00:32:19.350 --> 00:32:20.990
I'll avenge him!

463
00:32:20.990 --> 00:32:22.120
Wait, Ace!

464
00:32:23.530 --> 00:32:25.330
Drop it, you little shit!

465
00:32:25.760 --> 00:32:27.300
Get off me...

466
00:32:27.300 --> 00:32:28.500
Outta my way!

467
00:32:28.500 --> 00:32:33.040
You talk pretty big for a weakling like yourself!

468
00:32:33.040 --> 00:32:36.670
What can you even do?!
You'll just wind up dead!

469
00:32:36.670 --> 00:32:41.780
You'll die, and people will forget you by tomorrow
because you still haven't amounted to anything!

470
00:32:42.810 --> 00:32:47.350
It was this country—
this world—that killed Sabo!

471
00:32:47.350 --> 00:32:49.790
What can you do?!

472
00:32:50.920 --> 00:32:53.820
Your father's death brought about a new era!

473
00:32:53.820 --> 00:32:59.030
When you become a man of his caliber,
you can die whenever the hell you please!

474
00:33:02.630 --> 00:33:04.730
Go tie this moron up!

475
00:33:04.730 --> 00:33:06.030
Y-Yes, ma'am!

476
00:33:06.800 --> 00:33:10.640
Sabo!

477
00:33:10.640 --> 00:33:11.640
Damn it!

478
00:33:14.010 --> 00:33:18.980
Shut up! Men aren't supposed
to cry like that, Luffy!

479
00:33:34.560 --> 00:33:37.400
Have you cooled your head a bit, Ace?

480
00:33:41.200 --> 00:33:42.700
Untie him.

481
00:33:42.700 --> 00:33:43.440
– Yes, ma'am.
– Yes, ma'am.

482
00:33:45.140 --> 00:33:46.510
Let me untie you.

483
00:33:46.810 --> 00:33:47.940
Where's Luffy?

484
00:33:47.940 --> 00:33:49.810
He cried all night. He's asleep now.

485
00:33:51.850 --> 00:33:54.850
Boss! You have to see this!

486
00:33:54.850 --> 00:33:57.720
I-It's a letter! From Sabo!

487
00:33:56.050 --> 00:34:00.660
"To my brothers at Mt. Colubo - Sabo"

488
00:33:57.720 --> 00:34:00.660
He must have sent a letter
before setting out to sea!

489
00:34:02.220 --> 00:34:02.890
Give me that.

490
00:34:03.190 --> 00:34:07.260
I swear I won't go into the city.
That letter is addressed to us, right?

491
00:34:13.740 --> 00:34:18.040
Ace. Luffy. I hope you weren't hurt in the fire.

492
00:34:18.040 --> 00:34:20.910
I'm worried, but I'm sure you're okay.

493
00:34:21.680 --> 00:34:27.180
I'm sorry, guys, but by the time you
get this letter, I'll already be...

494
00:34:28.450 --> 00:34:30.050
out at sea.

495
00:34:31.250 --> 00:34:35.020
A lot has happened, so I decided
to set sail ahead of you guys.

496
00:34:40.560 --> 00:34:44.880
My destination is anywhere but this country.

497
00:34:45.830 --> 00:34:47.940
There, I will become stronger.

498
00:34:48.800 --> 00:34:50.120
I'll become a pirate!

499
00:34:51.770 --> 00:34:54.180
Let's become the most free pirates ever,

500
00:34:54.180 --> 00:34:57.280
and then the three of us
should meet up again someday.

501
00:34:58.350 --> 00:35:03.850
Somewhere out on the vast open sea...
We'll definitely meet again!

502
00:35:06.190 --> 00:35:07.620
Oh, and Ace...

503
00:35:08.420 --> 00:35:11.630
I wonder who's the older brother
between the two of us?

504
00:35:12.260 --> 00:35:15.260
Two big brothers and one little brother...

505
00:35:16.930 --> 00:35:20.540
Maybe it's strange,
but our bond is my treasure.

506
00:35:26.040 --> 00:35:30.360
Luffy might still be a weak crybaby, but...

507
00:35:36.550 --> 00:35:38.470
he's our little brother!

508
00:35:39.020 --> 00:35:40.420
Take care of him for me!
